<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-651-160  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 651 160.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  Sept 11 1989 v10 n36 p29(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Technical support shifts to consultative role.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Leinfuss, Emily.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Technical support is shifting toward a consultative role as endusers become more sophisticated and have different needs.andP;  Manytechnical-support specialists who once helped novice users withsimple difficulties now work directly with customers' businessunits, doing research and development on new technologies andadvising end users on business problems.andP;  The technical supportarea is undergoing reorganization in many companies, and MISdepartments are migrating people out to business units orretraining personnel.andP;  Today's information centers now hireindividuals with a broader range of skills because consultingdemands more than technical ability.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Support ServicesConsultantsTrendsBusiness PlanningOrganization Structure.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>